        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-02-11T16:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-02-11T16:05:00-05:00" n="19"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <head>19. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Switzerland</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d19fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 795.00/2–1155. Secret. Drafted by <persName>Jones</persName>, cleared
                        with <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_UNP1"
                            >UNP</gloss>, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_MCRJC1"
                            >McClurkin</persName>. Also sent to Stockholm and repeated to Seoul and
                        Tokyo.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-02-11T16:05:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1955—4:05 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1066. Tokyo also pass <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>. Our 510 to
                    Seoul repeated Bern 1052 Stockholm 591 and Tokyo 1583.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d19fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> Department officers met separately
                    Swiss and Swedish representatives February 10.<note n="3" xml:id="d19fn3"
                        >Memoranda of these conversations are in Department of State, Central Files,
                        795.00/2–1055.</note> Explained Sixteen believed unlikely Communists agree
                    preferred alternative liquidation <gloss target="#t_NNSC1">NNSC</gloss> but some
                    indication Communists might accept some form reduction personnel. Sixteen
                    therefore hope Swiss and Swedes make available on confidential basis detailed
                    proposals reduction personnel <gloss target="#t_NNSC1">NNSC</gloss> for
                    discussion with Sixteen February 18. Swiss and Swedish representatives agreed
                    make this request their governments. Also agreed put to their governments
                    question possible desirability asking Chinese Communists reaction
                    aide-mémoire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
